body.p:
To hide the TOC, you have multiple options:

Use a DITA bookmap instead of a DITA map, and omit the toc
          element from the booklists. An example bookmap can be found in
          the DITA 1.3 Spec. This is the best approach.

Use the transformation parameter: hide.frontpage.toc.index.glossary.

Use a display:none property to hide the element that contains the TOC
          structure, and also remove it from the PDF bookmarks
          tree:*[class ~= "map/map"] > *[class ~= "toc/toc"] {
  display:none;
}

*[class ~= "map/map"] > *[class ~= "toc/toc"] > *[class ~= "toc/title"]{
  bookmark-label: none;	
  -ah-bookmark-label: none;
}
